<TITLE> RanksTel latest to be caught for 'illegal VoIP' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 19 (bdnews24.com)  Private land phone operator RanksTel Thursday night became the third telephone company to be caught in BRTC's drive against illegal VoIP operations in under a week. Three RanksTel officials were detained following an overnight drive by the telecoms regulator, which uncovered evidence of the company's involvement in operating unlicensed Voice over Internet Protocol operations. Elite force Rapid Action Battalion assisted Bangladesh Telecommunications Regulatory Commission officials during the drive. RAB intelligence division chief Lt Col Ziaul Ahsan said VoIP appliances were seized from the RanksTel's office at Novo Tower in the capital's Tejgaon industrial area. He told bdnews24.com that RanksTel general manager (engineering) Sheikh Kamruzzaman, deputy general manager (engineering) Mominur Rahman Chowdhury and deputy general manager (sales) Iqbal Karim Bhuiyan Noman were detained for questioning. The telecoms regulator found similar evidence of illegal operations against two other telephone companies - Dhaka Phone and WorldTel on Mar 14 and Mar 16. Five top executives of Dhaka Phone officials were sent to jail after being arrested on charges of running unlicensed VoIP operations. bdn
